{#- â•â•â• INDUSTRY · CONSTRUCTION (BASELINE, equity-gated). t-mofu→t-prose / dc-base. Every
    baseline heading verbatim at its level; all prose carried, no thinning. #acctind-construction-definition
    preserved (speakable #1). ai-summary + faq rendered by t-prose (sec.aiH/faqH) — the layout
    emits #acctind-construction-ai-summary == speakable #2. vs-table→.cmp. founder-name-zero. â•â•â• -#}

{#- DEFINITION — speakable target, id preserved. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-construction-definition">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In plain terms</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Construction accounting, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- CHALLENGES — 3 dc-cards (H2 + 3 H3s). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-construction-challenges" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why contractor books break</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Three places contractors lose the numbers.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Profitable-looking companies go under when these go unmanaged. Knowing which one you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ c.signal | safe }}</span><h3>{{ c.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ c.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- WHAT WE HANDLE — the six services (H2 + 6 H3s). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-construction-handle">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What TechBrot handles</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Construction accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Every engagement is scoped to your jobs and crew, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.num | safe }}</span><h3><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.title | safe }}</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INTEGRATIONS — construction stack reconciled with QuickBooks (H2: Connected to how you build.). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-construction-integrations" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Tools we work alongside</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Connected to how you build.</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      {%- for t in integrations %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose">{{ integrationsNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- REVENUE-RECOGNITION TABLE — vs-table→.cmp. Supports definition prose. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-construction-methods">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How revenue is recognized</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Percentage-of-completion vs. completed-contract.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:72ch;">Which method you use changes how every job reads on your financials. We set up your books for the right one and keep the WIP behind it accurate.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">Construction revenue-recognition methods compared</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Consideration</th><th scope="col" class="num us">Percentage-of-completion</th><th scope="col">Completed-contract</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Consideration">When revenue is recognized</th><td class="num us" data-col="Percentage-of-completion">As the job progresses, by cost or milestone</td><td data-col="Completed-contract">Only when the job is finished</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Consideration">WIP schedule required</th><td class="num us" data-col="Percentage-of-completion"><span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span></td><td data-col="Completed-contract"><span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Consideration">Best for</th><td class="num us" data-col="Percentage-of-completion">Long, multi-period jobs &amp; bonded work</td><td data-col="Completed-contract">Short jobs &amp; smaller contractors</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Consideration">Profit visibility mid-job</th><td class="num us" data-col="Percentage-of-completion"><span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span></td><td data-col="Completed-contract"><span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Consideration">Tax-method eligibility</th><td class="num us" data-col="Percentage-of-completion">Often required above gross-receipts threshold</td><td data-col="Completed-contract">Available to many small contractors &mdash; confirm with your CPA</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PROCESS — four-phase engagement rhythm → process-grid (H2 + 4 H3s). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-construction-process" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How engagements work</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">From guesswork to job-level profit.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">Every construction engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; books accurate first, profit visibility second, advisory third.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">{{ s.num | safe }}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ADVISORY — standing brand line as H2; body carried as prose (no gutting). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-construction-advisory">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Beyond the books</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Accurate job costs are the start. Winning bids is the point.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;margin-top:26px;">
      <a class="btn btn-cta" href="/contact/?intent=accounting" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:48px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:11px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- EXPERT REVIEW — firm-level byline (founder-name-zero). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acctind-construction-review" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="byline">
      <span class="byline__mark"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 64 64" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"/><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"/></svg></span>
      <div><p class="byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p><p class="byline__meta">TechBrot Inc. &middot; independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot actually handles construction engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for technical accuracy on job costing, WIP, retainage, AIA progress billing, and certified payroll. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. TechBrot delivers the books and coordinates with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-15</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-15</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-15 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- RELATED — services & industries (H2 + 4 H3s). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="acctind-construction-related">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Related services &amp; industries.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ r.href }}"><h3>{{ r.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ (r.cta | replace(" &rarr;", "") | replace("&rarr;", "")) | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
